    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A thicker and slightly stiffer form of railroad board; six-ply and eight-ply are the common thicknesses. Poster board is typically covered on only one side with either white or colored paper.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
